/p>\n<p>I went to the site you mentionned and tested my site against it from various locations around the world: <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.webpagetest.org/">http://www.webpagetest.org/</a>. I noticed they have a forums <a rel="nofollow" target="_blank" href="http://www.webpagetest.org/forums/">http://www.webpagetest.org/forums/</a>. I found it interesting to be able to test my site from various areas of the world. I''m not sure I understood everything about the result I obtained there. I''ll have to read more of what they say in order to grasp what I saw.\n</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/eNpZE0VrJpo" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:87:"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/speedperformance-scores-go-up-and-down#post-7448063";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:2:{s:0:"";a:5:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:92:"danielgarneau on &quot;All In One WP Security &amp; Firewall plugin vs Jetpack Protect&quot;";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:118:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~3/ogxihFhhJ5Y/all-in-one-wp-security-firewall-plugin-vs-jetpack-protect-1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Sat, 19 Sep 2015 13:36:20 PDT";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"7447671@http://wordpress.org/support/";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:838:"<p>I have been using All In One WP Security &#38; Firewall for several months now and it has proved very stable. Amongst other things, it allows to change login access from wp-login to whatever you choose. </p>\n<p>I also use WordFence, another WordPress security plugin with complementary functionalities. WordFence allows me to see who attempted to login into my site. Renaming from wp-login to something else stopped these attacks. WordFence has a functionality that allows me to view all recent attempts to login to my site.</p>\n<p>I have jetpacked installed, but I am not using the protect module. Since I discovered Jetpack, I tend to try its modules before loading other plug-ins. But sometimes other plugins offer more options.\n</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/W3TOTALCACHE/~4/ogxihFhhJ5Y" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:108:"https://wordpress.org/support/topic/all-in-one-wp-security-firewall-plugin-vs-jetpack-protect-1#post-7447671";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:1:{s:4:"link";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:3:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"self";s:4:"type";s:19:"application/rss+xml";s:4:"href";s:40:"http://feeds.feedburner.com/W3TOTALCACHE";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:2:{s:3:"rel";s:4:"next";s:4:"href";s:93:"http://pipes.yahoo.com/pipes/pipe.run?_id=02f556aa2f503be89aa9d89723644f40&_render=rss&page=2";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"da